<span id="xv.iv.iv.cix-p1"></span> <span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.cix-p1.1"></span>Canon CVIII.  (Greek cxii.)</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cix-p2"></span>Synod against the heresy of Pelagius
and Celestius.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cix-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.cix-p3.1"></span>In</span> the consulate of the most
glorious Emperors, Honorius for the <span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.cix-p3.2"></span>XII</span>th time and Theodosius for the
<span class="sc"><span id="xv.iv.iv.cix-p3.3"></span>VIII</span>th,
Augusti most exalted, on the Calends of May, at Carthage in the
secretarium of the Basilica of Faustus.  When Aurelius the bishop
presided over the whole council, the deacons standing by, it pleased all
the bishops, whose names and subscriptions are indicated, <span
id="fr_479"></span>[480](#fn_479.md) met together in the holy synod of the
Church of Carthage to define— <span id="fr_480"></span>[481](#fn_480.md)

